<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Pia Miller and her multi-millionaire American talent agent boyfriend Patrick Whitesell reunited in Sydney last week, after being separated for months amid the pandemic. </p>

<p>And on Sunday, the couple appeared to be making up for lost time as they enjoyed a date night at the former Home and Away star's eastern suburbs home.</p>

<p>The actress, 36, shared photos of their romantic set-up to her Instagram Stories, including one which saw her 55-year-old beau grilling on the barbecue.  </p>

<p>Reunited: Pia Miller, 36, made up for lost time with her American multi-millionaire agent boyfriend Patrick Whitesell, 55, on Sunday, after finally reuniting amid the pandemic's strict international border closures. Pictured in a prior Instagram post </p>

<p>'One of those nights! Home sweet home,' Pia captioned a picture of the barbecue lit up, and stationed next to the outdoor pool.</p>

<p>A second image, which Pia adorned with a drawn-on love heart, saw a casually dressed Patrick cooking what looked to be sausages.</p>

<p>In an Instagram photo last Wednesday, Pia was positively glowing as she sat next to Patrick in a car, after having spent months apart on opposite sides of the globe.   </p>

<p>Date night: 'One of those nights! Home sweet home,' the former Home and Away star captioned a picture of the barbecue at her Sydney home lit up, and stationed next to the outdoor pool, on her Instagram Stories </p>

<p>Her love: A second image, which Pia adorned with a drawn-on love heart, saw a casually dressed Patrick cooking what looked to be sausages </p>

<p>'Can't keep us apart! Two Ps in a pod,' Pia wrote online, adding a love heart emoji.  </p>

<p>With the coronavirus pandemic prompting international border closures, Pia has been living in Sydney while Patrick has been based in Los Angeles. </p>

<p>As evidenced by her Instagram, they were last together in February, when Pia visited her beau at his LA mansion.   </p>

<p>Together again! In an Instagram photo last Wednesday (pictured), Pia was glowing as she sat next to Patrick in a car, after having spent months apart on opposite sides of the globe </p>

<p>Loved-up: In March, the actress shared a throwback photo of the pair during a romantic holiday in Italy</p>

<p>Stepping out: The couple made their red carpet debut at the Academy Awards held in Los Angeles in February this year </p>

<p>Pia was first linked to the Hollywood power agent in August last year, following her split with her longtime fiancé, Tyson Mullane, 31. </p>

<p>The couple made their public debut at a Halloween party in Los Angeles in October, amid reports they'd started dating back in May.</p>

<p>She finally made their relationship 'Instagram Official' on Christmas Eve, sharing a loved-up photo with Patrick outside of the Louvre in Paris, and captioning it 'P²'.</p>

<p>The couple made their red carpet debut at this year's Academy Awards held in Los Angeles in February. </p>

<p>Going public: Pia made their relationship 'Instagram Official' on Christmas Eve. She shared a loved-up photo with Patrick outside of the Louvre in Paris, captioning it 'P²'</p>
